</div>'),
(2400, '2006-07-11', 'The Ship Available Now Via Steam', '<div class=\"post_content\" id=\"content_685\" style=\"display: none;\">
<p>The Ship, a massively mysterious thriller (MMT) from Outerlight Ltd, is available now via Steam, Valve\'s electronic distribution platform. Set onboard a 1920\'s luxury liner, Mr X, the Ship\'s owner has \"invited\" you to a mysterious multiplayer game of hunt and hunted, as players must secretly track and extinguish specified passengers while avoiding similar fate. The ship is available for just $19.95. <a href=\"http://storefront.steampowered.com/v2/index.php?area=game&amp;AppId=2400\">Click here</a> for more details.</p>
<br clear=\"left\"/>
</div>'),
(2400, '2006-07-12', 'The Ship Update Released', '<div class=\"post_content\" id=\"content_688\" style=\"display: none;\">
<p>Updates to The Ship have been released. The updates will be applied automatically when your Steam client is restarted. The specific changes include:<br/><br/><b>The Ship</b><br/><ul style=\"padding-bottom: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;\"><li>Dedicated servers will now be able to see the SteamId of players</li></ul></p>
<br clear=\"left\"/>
</div>'),
(2400, '2006-07-17', NULL, '<div class=\"details\" id=\"July 17, 2006\" style=\"display: none;\">
Changes/Additions
	<ul>
<li> Weapon fines and sentences balanced</li> <li> Default witness count set to 2</li> <li> Default witness time set to 1 second</li> <li> Scoreboard is no longer showable whilst in court, and no longer gets stuck up when leaving court</li> <li> Hunters who have already killed their quarry no longer get a \"Quarry Reassigned\" message when their old quarry leaves the game</li> <li> Pee sounds tweaked</li> <li> Increased the cost of bribing guards to ignore security breaches</li> <li> Increased the cost of healing at sickbay</li> <li> Balanced ambient soundscapes in various maps</li> <li> Players can now click-through the court screen to start serving their sentence immediately</li> <li> Players can now chat with others while in court</li> <li> Players who now set others on fire when they are burning get accredited for the kill correctly</li> </ul>
Bug fixes
	<ul>
<li> Fixed a number of server stability issues</li> <li> Fixed breaking-down doors</li> <li> Fixed occasional map-wide jumping problem (jump going in random direction)</li> <li> Fixed context sensitive interface (CSI) positioning issues in all aspect ratios</li> <li> Fixed containers getting stuck open when the player using them is killed</li> <li> Fixed container/shop/CSI panels that were left shown to a player when that player dies</li> <li> Fixed attachments not being removed from the player model when they are dropped from the inventory</li> <li> Fixed water dripping from hands on other players</li> <li> Correct water effect for different sized sinks</li> <li> Correct sounds added to the metal pressure doors</li> </ul>
</div>'),
(2400, '2006-07-17', 'The Ship Update Released', '<div class=\"post_content\" id=\"content_690\" style=\"display: none;\">
<p>Updates to The Ship have been released. The updates will be applied automatically when your Steam client is restarted.</p>
<br clear=\"left\"/>
</div>'),
(2400, '2006-07-20', 'The Ship Update Released', '<div class=\"post_content\" id=\"content_696\" style=\"display: none;\">
<p>Updates to The Ship have been released. The updates will be applied automatically when your Steam client is restarted. The specific changes include:<br/><br/><b>The Ship</b><br/><ul style=\"padding-bottom: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;\"><li>A number of server stability fixes<br/><li>Fixed weapon ammo amount when dropped from inventory<br/><li>Money for kills values for weapons are now halved (by default) as soon as a weapon is used (and each time thereafter) within a round, and then reset to the minimum value at the end of a round<br/><li>Fixed visual effects being played when they shouldn\'t (e.g. dripping hands)<br/><li>Fixed flames being left behind when player arrested<br/><li>\'/\' characters now work within chat</li></li></li></li></li></li></ul></p>
<br clear=\"left\"/>
</div>'),
(2400, '2006-08-01', NULL, '<div class=\"details\" id=\"August 1, 2006\" style=\"display: none;\">
Changes/Additions
	<ul>
<li> Added Linux Dedicated Server (Beta)</li> <li> Tightened Kick/Ban system defaults</li> <li> Added console chat for admins</li> <li> Lighting on characters improved</li> <li> Increased warm-up time before game begins on a server from 30 to 60 seconds</li> <li> Axe containers now appear empty when no axe is in them</li> </ul>
Bug fixes
	<ul>
<li> Fixed a number of client and server stability issues</li> <li> Fixed ERRORNAME bug</li> <li> Fix for suicide exploit - suicide via the \'kill\' command has a 60 second delay</li> <li> Fixed another version of the dripping hands bug</li> <li> Fixed incorrect MFK displayed in inventory, shops and containers for purse bomb</li> <li> Added missing fallback water textures for older video cards</li> <li> Fixed hands disappearing from a few player models</li> <li> Fixed bug to maintain bot presence on a server</li> <li> Fixed bug where you were given different hat/glasses/hair when not killed by your Hunter</li> </ul>
</div>'),
(2400, '2006-08-01', 'The Ship Update Released', '<div class=\"post_content\" id=\"content_712\" style=\"display: none;\">
<p>Updates to The Ship have been released. The updates will be applied automatically when your Steam client is restarted. The specific changes include:<br/><br/><b>The Ship</b><br/><ul style=\"padding-bottom: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;\"><li>Fixed a number of client and server stability issues<br/><li>Added Linux Dedicated Server (Beta)<br/><li>Fixed ERRORNAME bug<br/><li>Tightened Kick/Ban system defaults<br/><li>Added console chat for admins<br/><li>Fix for suicide exploit - suicide via the \'kill\' command has a 60 second delay<br/><li>Fixed another version of the dripping hands bug<br/><li>Fixed incorrect MFK displayed in inventory, shops and containers for purse bomb<br/><li>Added missing fallback water textures for older video cards<br/><li>Fixed hands disappearing from a few player models<br/><li>Lighting on characters improved<br/><li>Fixed bug to maintain bot presence on a server<br/><li>Fixed bug where you were given different hat/glasses/hair when not killed by your Hunter<br/><li>Increased warm-up time before game begins on a server from 30 to 60 seconds<br/><li>Axe containers now appear empty when no axe is in them</li></li></li></li></li></li></li></li></li></li></li></li></li></li></li></ul></p>
<br clear=\"left\"/>
</div>'),
